Transcription.Text: The day was approached by seven steps, carpeted in blue velvet embroidered with golden fleurs-de-lis. Around the days were his subordinates, each in a position appropriate to his rank. In this new context, the ceremonial bed, or lite the parade, became an acceptet part of social life in Western Europe from early renaissance times until the - French revolution.
